    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-14T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="49"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/5–1446: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular Officers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="46" xml:id="d49fn1">At Bangkok, London, Moscow, Nanking, Paris, and
                        Saigon.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-14T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 14, 1946—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Vietnam Republic’s President believes satisfactory agreement can be reached with
                    French, expressed confidence their good faith in Hanoi Paris but disturbed by
                    French actions Saigon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
